%T A397538 55188522879,646444827518,7595842590100,89493336404547,
%U A397538 1056870473870115,12506725840238275,148269769382169375,1760605667665976931,20936254422667661407,249287812740855557714
%N A397538 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} binomial(2*n+3*k-4,k).
%F A397538 G.f.: 1/(g^4 * (1-5*x*g^4) * (1-x*g^2)) where g = 1+x*g^5 is the g.f. of A002294.
%F A397538 G.f.: 1/((5-4*g) * (1-g+g^3)) where g = 1+x*g^5 is the g.f. of A002294.
%F A397538 Here and below, binomial(N,k) = 0 for k<0.
%F A397538 This is the special case l=2, m=3, c=0, r=1, s=0 of the following family. For integers l, m, c in Z, and for any constants r and s, define a_{l,m,c,r,s}(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} (r*binomial(l*n+m*k-m-1+c,k) - s*binomial(l*n+m*k-m-1+c,k-1)). A_{l,m,c,r,s}(x) = Sum_{n>=0} a_{l,m,c,r,s}(n)*x^n = t^c*(r+s-s*t)/((l+m-(l+m-1)*t)*(1-t+t^m)), where t = t(x) satisfies t = 1 + x*t^(l+m), equivalently y = x*(1+y)^(l+m) with y=t-1.
%o A397538 (PARI) a(n) = sum(k=0, n, binomial(2*n+3*k-4, k));
%Y A397538 Cf. A165817, A397510, A397539, A397540.
%Y A397538 Cf. A002294, A397541.
